# {{ project_name }}

Generated by **perfectRAG** — template `code-graph-rag`.

Code intelligence for AI coding agents (Claude Code / Cursor). Unlike naive
vector code-RAG, this gives the agent **precise, structural** navigation:
symbols, references, call hierarchy — the things grep can't do reliably.

## Stack

| Component | Choice |
|---|---|
| Primary code intel | **Serena** (LSP, 30+ languages, no infrastructure) |
| Structural search | **ast-grep** (AST pattern match/rewrite) |
| Optional graph store | Memgraph + Lab UI (`docker compose up`) |
| Optional semantic search | `claude-context` (Milvus) — `perfectrag add mcp claude-context` |
| Chunking (if embedding) | {{ recipe.chunk_strategy }} / {{ recipe.chunk_size }} tokens |

## Quickstart — wire into Claude Code (no Docker needed)

1. Set the repo you want indexed:

   ```bash
   export REPO_PATH=/path/to/your/repo   # defaults to the current dir
   ```

2. Register `mcp.yaml` with Claude Code (it launches Serena via `uvx` on demand).
   Then ask things like *"find all references to `recommend`"* or *"show the call
   hierarchy of `render`"* — answered by symbols, not guesses.

`perfectrag list mcp` shows more code-intel servers; add with `perfectrag add mcp <name>`.

## Optional — persistent code graph

```bash
docker compose up -d            # Memgraph (bolt :7687) + Lab UI (:3000)
```

Index your repo into Memgraph with a graph indexer such as
[code-graph-rag](https://github.com/vitali87/code-graph-rag), then explore the
AST/call graph at `http://localhost:3000`. This is opt-in — Serena alone covers
most day-to-day navigation.

